OL,3,CKevin Keegan reveals stage four cancer
OL,4,Cdiagnosis
OL,6,FKeegan began his career with
OL,7,FScunthorpe and was signed by Liverpool
OL,8,Fin 1971, winning the First Division
OL,9,Fthree times along with two UEFA Cups,
OL,10,Fthe FA Cup and the 1977 European Cup.
OL,12,FHe won the Ballon d'Or ` then called
OL,13,Fthe European Footballer of the Year `
OL,14,Ftwice while at German side Hamburg,
OL,15,Fwhere he featured in another European
OL,16,FCup final, and played for Southampton
OL,17,Fand Newcastle before retiring in 1984.
OL,19,FOn the international stage, he scored
OL,20,F21 goals in 63 England appearances and
OL,21,Fplayed at the 1982 World Cup finals.
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}        G4/6
